Summary

Telstra Corporation Limited (Telstra) is an Australia-based company, providing telecommunications and information services for domestic and international customers. The Company operates in eight business segments: Telstra Consumer Marketing and Channels, Telstra Business, Telstra International, Telstra Operations, Telstra Wholesale, Sensis and Other (including Telstra BigPond, Telstra Media, Telstra Country Wide, Strategic Marketing and its corporate areas). On June 22, 2007, Telstra acquired an additional 25% ownership interest in 1300 Australia Pty. On June 5, 2007, its controlled entity KAZ Group Pty Limited purchased the remaining 40% shareholding in Enhanced Processing Technologies Pty Ltd. In June 2008, the Company announced that it has acquired 55% of two Chinese Internet businesses, Norstar Media and Autohome/PCPop.
